 …to show his devotion to her after she died from breast cancer A man in China has married his partner’s corpse during her funeral to show his love for her after she lost her battle with breast cancer. The heart-broken groom, 35-year-old Xu Shinan, hoped that the wedding ceremony could realise his late fiancée’s dream of being a bride. Xu’s deceased partner of 12 years, Yang Liu, was dressed in a white bridal gown and surrounded by 169 bouquets pink roses when Xu read his wedding vows to her, according to a local report. Continue reading Heart-broken fiancé marries partner’s corpse during her funeral at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard